       <h1><a name="Two"style="font-weight: 40">Works</a></h1>
<div id="workstext">
        <p> My style is heavily inspired by my Chinese heritage and the tranquil and beautiful elements of nature.
        I offer both temporary and permanent tattoos, suitable for all ranges of skin tones and body types.
        Here is a little sneak peek into how I design and tattoo my own custom hand drawn tattoos.
</p>
</div>

<h3 style="font-weight: 50"> Design Process </h3>

<div id="designpro">
        <p>My design process always starts out with composing a list of the elements, concepts, and colour palettes the client gives me. Browsing Pinterest, Instagram, VSCO, to help me ideate and visualize the tattoo. Then, I look at the placement and determine any flattering shapes that would help contour the body (whilst keeping in mind the elements to include). I would build out my image with blobs and rough sketches, before developing it's features. When I am ready for the features, I load up my sketch into my iPad and use procreate with an A4 document to draw out my design. Each and every one of my tattoo stencils have been hand-drawn, the maximize detail and precision in my tattoos. </p>

</div>

